%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20announced%20a%20new%20smartwatch%20aimed%20at%20kids%20ages%207%20and%20up%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Fitbit%20Ace%20LTE.%20The%20watch%20can%20call%20and%20text%20parents%20over%20LTE%20service%20(with%20a%20data%20plan)%2C%20and%20parents%20can%20track%20their%20kids%20through%20GPS.%20There's%20also%20some%20gamified%20activity%20tracking%20for%20the%20kids.%20(It%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-fitbit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFitbit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20after%20all.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20first%20reported%20in%202022%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproject-eleven-google-wearable-pre-teens-health-safety-features-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20was%20working%20on%20a%20wearable%20device%20for%20preteens%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20kid%20having%20a%20smartwatch%20sounds%20ridiculous%20to%20you%2C%20you%20probably%20don't%20have%20a%20kid%20between%20the%20ages%20of%206%20and%2013.%20Lots%20of%20parents%20are%20looking%20for%20a%20way%20to%20be%20able%20to%20call%20or%20track%20their%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20without%20giving%20them%20an%20actual%20phone.%20Smartwatches%20have%20become%20a%20popular%20way%20to%20hold%20off%20on%20giving%20kids%20a%20full%20phone%20until%20they're%20older%20while%20allowing%20them%20some%20independence%20to%20roam%20freely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fitbit%20Ace%20LTE%20works%20over%20LTE%20and%20requires%20a%20data%20plan%2C%20but%20not%20an%20extra%20phone%20line.%20It%20can%20call%20and%20text%20up%20to%2020%20people%20entered%20as%20contacts%20into%20the%20device%20%E2%80%94%20but%20only%20to%20people%20who%20have%20the%20Fitbit%20Ace%20app%20installed%20on%20their%20phones.%20This%20means%20that%20kids%20don't%20have%20free%20range%20to%20call%20or%20text%20just%20anyone%20through%20the%20device%20(no%20calling%20for%20pizza%20delivery%2C%20for%20example).%20Only%20parents%20can%20access%20the%20GPS%20tracking%2C%20according%20to%20the%20specs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20Fitbit%2C%20so%20there's%20some%20activity%20tracking%20and%20gamification%20of%20movement%20and%20some%20video%20games%20that%20can%20be%20played%20with%20points%20for%20achieving%20fitness%20goals.%20(The%20video%20game%20can%20be%20deactivated%20during%20%26quot%3BSchool%20Time%26quot%3B%20mode.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20smartwatches%20out%20there%20aimed%20at%20the%20not-ready-for-a-phone%20age%20demographic%3A%20Verizon%20Gizmo%203%2C%20Garmin%20Bounce%2C%20and%20the%20Gabb%20Watch%203.%20Gabb%20is%20a%20company%20that%20only%20makes%20devices%20for%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20it%20also%20has%20a%20smartphone%20that%20is%20far%20more%20locked%20down%20in%20terms%20of%20privacy%20and%20safety%20for%20kids%20than%20the%20average%20phone%20(i.e.%2C%20no%20social%20media%20apps%20can%20be%20downloaded%3B%20no%20open%20internet%20browsing).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Apple%20Watch%20is%20slightly%20more%20fraught%20as%20a%20kid%20device%20since%20models%20with%20a%20cellular%20plan%20are%20more%20expensive%2C%20and%20parental%20controls%20that%20block%20social%20apps%20or%20internet%20use%20are%20more%20complicated%20to%20set%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fitbit%20Ace%20LTE%20is%20%24229%2C%20which%20is%20more%20expensive%20than%20some%20of%20its%20competitors.%20We%20haven't%20tested%20this%20yet%2C%20but%20based%20on%20the%20features%20and%20the%20images%20of%20the%20sleek%2C%20rounded%20design%2C%20and%20the%20screen%20images%20of%20the%20apps%20%E2%80%94%20it%20looks%20really%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-smartwatch-kids-fitbit-ace-lte-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717007348000%2