limate%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20KJ%20Ramesh%2C%20former%20Director%20General%20of%20Meteorology%20of%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%20(IMD)%2C%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIncrementally%2C%20some%20parts%20of%20urban%20areas%20will%20be%20hotter%20than%20the%20other%20due%20to%20heat%20island%20effect%2C%20and%20reduction%20of%20green%20cover%20will%20increase%20localised%20hotspots%20of%20extreme%20heat.%20That's%20how%20we%20are%20responsible%20for%20land%20cover%20changes...%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHeat%20island%20effect%20is%20the%20result%20of%20replacing%20natural%20land%20cover%20with%20heat-absorbing%20surfaces%20like%20buildings%2C%20pavement%2C%20and%20other%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEmitting%20air-conditioners%20add%20additional%20heat.%202%20degree%20Celsius%20of%20additional%20heat%20is%20added%20by%20ACs%2C%20we%20should%20not%20forget%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Ramesh%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Vivek%20Nangia%20of%20pulmonology%20at%20Max%20Super%20Speciality%20Hospital%20said%20when%20exposed%20to%20very%20high%20temperature%2C%20the%20body%20loses%20fluid%20and%20electrolytes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20result%2C%20it%20will%20start%20with%20simple%20signs%20like%20heat%20rash%2C%20going%20on%20to%20people%20developing%20heat%20cramps%2C%20body%20ache%2C%20getting%20tired%20by%20end%20of%20the%20day.%20It%20could%20worsen%20to%20what%20is%20called%20heat%20exhaustion%20where%20people%20could%20develop%20headache%2C%20nausea%20dizziness%2C%20weakness%2C%20immense%20thirst%2C%20heavy%20sweating...%20if%20the%20heat%20is%20too%20much%2C%20people%20may%20black%20out%20and%20just%20collapse.%20Blood%20pressure%20can%20drop%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20last%20stage%20is%20heat%20stroke%2C%20which%20can%20be%20fatal%20at%20times.%20When%20you%20have%20a%20heat%20stroke%2C%20that's%20the%20point%20the%20patient%20has%20high%20fever%2C%20profuse%20sweating%2C%20unresponsive%2C%20can%20be%20fatal%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr%20Nangia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi's%20primary%20weather%20station%20Safdarjung%20observatory%20recorded%20a%20maximum%20temperature%20of%2046.8%20degree%20Celsius%2C%20highest%20in%2079%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMD%20issued%20a%20red%20alert%20health%20notice%20for%20Delhi%2C%20with%20an%20estimated%20population%20of%20more%20than%2030%20million%20people.%20The%20alert%20warns%20there%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20high%20likelihood%20of%20developing%20heat%20illness%20and%20heat%20stroke%20in%20all%20ages%26quot%3B%2C%20with%20%26quot%3Bextreme%20care%20needed%20for%20vulnerable%20people%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20no%20stranger%20to%20searing%20summer%20temperatures%2C%20but%20years%20of%20scientific%20research%20have%20found%20climate%20change%20is%20causing%20heatwaves%20to%20become%20longer%2C%20more%20frequent%20and%20more%20intense.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716991680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F002u08u_delhi-heatwave-_625x300_27_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdelhi-hottest-day-starts-with-simple-signs-like-what-doctor-said-on-heat-stroke-5772933%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Experts%20have%20asked%20people%20to%20prepare%20to%20accept%20the%20real%20possibility%20of%20seeing%20record%20high%20temperatures.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdelhi-hottest-day-starts-with-simple-signs-like-what-doctor-said-on-heat-stroke-5772933%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdelhi-hottest-day-starts-with-simple-signs-like-what-doctor-said-on-heat-stroke-5772933%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdelhi-hottest-day-starts-with-simple-signs-like-what-doctor-said-on-heat-stroke-5772933%2Famp%2F1%22